==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uroerythrin
<hw>U`ro*e*ryth"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 1st
<er>Uro-</er>, and <er>Erythrin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld>
<def>A reddish urinary pigment, considered as the substance which gives
to the urine of rheumatism its characteristic color. It also causes the
red color often seen in deposits of urates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urogastric</ent>⟦br⟧
